'''Arieh O'Sullivan''' (born March 22, 1961) is an [[author]], [[journalist]] and an award-winning defense correspondent<ref>[http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1P1-3594107.html 'Post' reporter wins JDC journalism award]</ref> who has covered [[Israel]] and the [[Middle East]] for over two decades.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.themedialine.org/main/core.asp|title=The Media Line: Management and Staff|accessdate=27 May 2010}}</ref> He currently serves as the bureau chief of The Media Line, a non-profit American news agency covering the Middle East.<ref name="sjmc.umn.edu"/> He is best known for his former role as a  defense correspondent and analyst for ''[[The Jerusalem Post]]'', the Middle East's leading English daily,<ref name="abc.net.au">[http://www.abc.net.au/rn/mediareport/stories/2002/534566.htm Reporting the Middle East]</ref> where he worked for over 10 years.<ref name="cosmos.ucc.ie">[http://cosmos.ucc.ie/cs1064/jabowen/IPSC/php/authors.php?auid=1323 Arieh O'Sullivan, biographical details]</ref> He appears as a guest commentator on a variety of world radio and television news programs and has reported from the [[Palestinian territories]], [[Rwanda]], [[Kosovo]], [[Northern Ireland]], [[Lebanon]], [[Turkey]] and [[China]].<ref name="abc.net.au"/>

==Career==
Before joining ''The Jerusalem Post'', O'Sullivan worked for seven years as a correspondent for [[The Associated Press]] based in [[Jerusalem]] and covered the peace processes, the [[Gulf War]] in 1991, Palestinian unrest, the [[Assassination of Yitzhak Rabin|Rabin assassination]], immigration from [[Ethiopia]] as well as the civil war in Rwanda.<ref name="sjmc.umn.edu">[http://www.sjmc.umn.edu/news/reporter/index.php?entry=227287 Alumni Notes, University of Mississippi School of Journalism]</ref> He was a Knight Journalism fellow at [[Stanford University]] in 2002<U+2013>2003.<ref>[http://knight.stanford.edu/fellows/2003/index.html Knight Fellowships Class of 2003]</ref>

O'Sullivan also served as Director of Communications for the [[Anti-Defamation League|Anti-Defamation League's]] Israel office from 2006 to 2008.<ref name="sjmc.umn.edu"/><ref>[http://www.jewishnola.com/page.aspx?id=198372 Arieh O'Sullivan to speak]</ref>

==Personal life==
O<U+2019>Sullivan was raised in the US states of [[Louisiana]] and [[Mississippi]]<ref name="pajamasmedia">[http://pajamasmedia.com/blog/dad-knew-who-killed-jfk/ Dad Knew Who Killed JFK]</ref> and moved to Israel in 1981. He served as a paratrooper in the first Lebanon War and was discharged in 2008 from the reserves, where he had served as a liaison officer with the Jordanian, Egyptian and other foreign militaries.

He has a BA in Mass Communications from the [[University of Minnesota]].<ref name="sjmc.umn.edu"/>

He is also a founding member of the ecological village of [[Srigim]] in the [[Valley of Elah|Elah Valley]] in [[Central District (Israel)|central Israel]] where he lives with his wife and three children. He is an avid [[paragliding|paraglider]]<ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/culture/travel/high-on-life-1.250664 High on life]</ref><ref>[http://www.jpost.com/Magazine/Features/Article.aspx?id=259 Riding the holy wind]</ref> and grows [[Olive oil|olives]] for oil.<ref name="pajamasmedia"/>

